<p>The global workplace forces us to improve our communication skills. It includes emails, letters, reports, company brochures, presentation slides, case studies, sales materials, visual aids, social media updates, and other business documents.</p>
</div>
<button class="accordion">What are the 10 C's of business writing?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>The 10 C's of business writing include:</p>
<li>Complete</li>
<li>Correct</li>
<li>Concise</li>
<li>Coherent</li>
<li>Clear</li>
<li>Considerate</li>
<li>Conversational</li>
<li>Concrete</li>
<li>Courteous</li>
<li>Credible.</li><p></p>
</div>
<button class="accordion">How can I be a good business writer?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>Here are the seven tips for becoming a better business writer:</p>
<li>Use the active rather than passive voice</li>
<li>Avoid linking verbs</li>
<li>Try not to use the word "very"</li>
<li>Limit the word "that"</li>
<li>Write to the reader</li>
<li>Stay away from cliches and colloquialisms</li>
<li>Keep sentences short.</li>
</div>
<button class="accordion">What are business writing skills?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>Business writing is a type of writing that seeks to elicit a business response. It's a purposeful piece of writing that provides relevant information to help a reader know something or do something. It must be substantive, clear, correct, and easy to scan.</p>
</div>
<button class="accordion">What is a business writing format?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>Business documents such as letters, emails, memorandums and reports and use paragraphs to separate different types of information, arguments and ideas. Paragraphs written in business format are structured in a formal, professional and well-organised manner. Be consistent in the way you format your paragraphs.</p>
</div>
<button class="accordion">What are business writing principles?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>The five principles of effective business writing are:</p>
<li>Clear purpose</li>
<li>Clarity and conciseness</li>
<li>Awareness of audience</li>
<li>Appropriate tone</li>
<li>Attention to form.</li><p></p>
</div>
<button class="accordion">Why are business writing skills essential?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>Quality written communication is essential for good management. It helps employees sharpen their writing skills and prepares them to rise in the organisation.</p>
</div>
<button class="accordion">What is advanced business writing?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>The aim is to develop documents appropriate to the audience and purpose that are well-argued and conform to business writing standards. Topics include context, purpose, audience, style, organisation, format, results, technologies, and persuasion strategies in typical workplace messages.</p>
</div>
<button class="accordion">What is the tone in business writing?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>The tone in writing refers to the writer's attitude toward the reader and the message's subject. Business writers should consider their message's style, whether they are writing a memo, letter, report, or business document.</p>
